Introduction

BIKINY (formally known as GIRLFRIEND) was a four-member Korean pop girl group that debuted in 2012 under StarFactory. They debuted as BIKINY but changed their name to GIRLFRIEND for a short time until two members left and member LaLa was added, then returned to their original name. The group is presumably disbanded as they have been inactive since 2014.
